achatina.name: Achatina(玛瑙螺)
achatina.desc: The Achatina(玛瑙螺) is a massive snail, mostly used for its production of Cementing Paste, or as a pet. This creature produces its paste passively — and quite frequently — so many survivors keep them around their bases. However, its usefulness pretty much ends there, as it cannot attack and moves quite slow. The Achatina(玛瑙螺) must be tamed violently.

allosaurus.name: Allosaurus(异特龙)
allosaurus.desc: The Allosaurus(异特龙) is a pack-hunting theropod that's smaller but faster than Rex, and larger but slower than Carnotaurus. When in packs of 3 or more, the highest level Allosaurus(异特龙) will become the pack leader, emitting a red aura and making it stronger in battle.

ammonite.name: Ammonite(菊石)
ammonite.tamingNotice: The Ammonite(菊石) cannot be tamed.
ammonite.desc: While the Ammonite(菊石) cannot be tamed, it is often hunted as its bile can be used to make powerful antidotes.

archaeopteryx.name: Archaeopteryx(始祖鸟)
archaeopteryx.desc: The Archaeopteryx(始祖鸟) is a tree-dwelling bird-like dinosaur. While its smaller frame make it unfit for riding, it is strong enough to carry humans, allowing them to glide across long distances. Taming an Archaeopteryx(始祖鸟) is no simple task, as it will immediately flee when approached, and once knocked out, it prefers to eat rare insect matter.

attackdrone.name: Attack Drone(无人攻击机)
attackdrone.tamingNotice: This creature's Dododex profile may contain spoilers. Have a good strategy on how to battle the Attack Drone(无人攻击机)? Share a tip!

baryonyx.name: Baryonyx(重爪龙)
baryonyx.desc: The Baryonyx(重爪龙) is a large crocodile-like predator. While it might lack in attack power, its ability to swim extremtly fast makes it a fierce opponent — especially with its ability to travel on both land and in water.

basilisk.name: Basilisk(毒蜥)
basilisk.desc: The Basilisk(毒蜥) is a fearsome snake-like creature in Ark: Aberration.
basilisk.tamingNotice: To tame a Basilisk(毒蜥), you must feed it fertilized eggs.

basilosaurus.name: Basilosaurus(龙王鲸)
basilosaurus.desc: The Basilosaurus(龙王鲸) is a dolphin-like creature that primarily dwells along the shallow areas of the ocean. It has the ability to keep survivors warm or cool.

beelzebufo.name: Beelzebufo(魔鬼娃)
beelzebufo.desc: One of the island's most useful amphibians, the beelzebufo can create cementing paste in its stomach simply by eating insects. Incredibly fast when hopping, its jumps can traverse vast expanses at the cost of little to no stamina. The beelzebufo can swim especially well and is one of the few creatures that can cause torpor using its attack. While it may be a little difficult to tame safely, many survivors consider it an especially useful addition to their tribes.

bulbdog.name: Bulbdog(灯泡犬)
bulbdog.desc: The Bulbdog(灯泡犬) (originally referred to as a 'Lantern Pug') is a cute bulldog-like creature in Ark: Aberration with a glowing orb antenna. The Bulbdog(灯泡犬) can be carried on a human's shoulder. It is a passive tame.

brontosaurus.name: Brontosaurus(雷龙)
brontosaurus.desc: The Brontosaurus(雷龙) is a behemoth of a dinosaur with a powerful tail 'tail sweep' attack that can smash all nearby enemies. This method is also one of the most efficient ways to gather berries and thatch, and the Brontosaurus(雷龙)' ability to carry large quantities of items make it even more useful for gathering. With its ability to carry a Platform Saddle, the Brontosaurus(雷龙) is often considered a must-have dinosaur for nomadic tribes looking for a mobile base.

broodmotherlysrix.name: Broodmother(育母蜘蛛)
broodmotherlysrix.tamingNotice: The Broodmother(育母蜘蛛) is one of the three bosses. Have a good strategy on how to battle Broodmother(育母蜘蛛)? Share a tip!

chalicotherium.name: Chalicotherium(砂犷兽)
chalicotherium.desc: The Chalicotherium(砂犷兽) is a mammal commonly found in colder areas that many survivors find useful in battle. In the wild, Chalicotherium(砂犷兽) often playfully throw snowballs and mud rocks at each other, however, when tamed, they can be given boulders to throw at enemy structures.

cnidaria.name: Cnidaria(水母)
cnidaria.tamingNotice: The Cnidaria(水母) cannot be tamed.
cnidaria.desc: The Cnidaria(水母) is a small jellyfish found in the deepest depths of the oceans. This easy-to-spot creature won't attack unless approached too closely. It delivers a sedative sting that can knock out enemies if striked repeatedly. While it cannot be tamed, survivors will hunt it to gather its sedative, which is used for advanced tranquilizers.

coelacanth.name: Coelacanth(腔棘鱼)
coelacanth.tamingNotice: The Coelacanth(腔棘鱼) can only be tamed using a Fish Basket in Aberration.

daeodon.name: Daeodon(凶齿豨)
daeodon.desc: The Daeodon(凶齿豨) (or 'Hell Pig') is a vicious pig. This pig has a high healing and food consumption rate, making it difficult to maintain. It can be tamed and ridden, however, taming it is quite a difficult task.

deathworm.name: Deathworm(死亡蠕虫)
deathworm.tamingNotice: The Deathworm(死亡蠕虫) is not tamable. It can be found in the outer deserts of Scorched Earth. Have a good strategy on how to battle it? Share a tip!

defenseunit.name: Defense Unit(防御守卫)
defenseunit.tamingNotice: This creature's Dododex profile may contain spoilers. Have a good strategy on how to battle the Defense Unit(防御守卫)? Share a tip!

dilophosaur.name: Dilophosaur(双脊龙)
dilophosaur.desc: A Dilophosaur(双脊龙) is a small, relatively weak dinosaur. Still, they're easy to tame for newer survivors, and are not hard to manage. They serve as guard dogs or pack-hunters, but are easily killed. Don't get too attached to them, as they likely won't survive combat against stronger dinosaurs.

diplocaulus.name: Diplocaulus(笠头螈)
diplocaulus.desc: The Diplocaulus(笠头螈) is a swamp amphibian with one major use once tamed; becoming a living oxygen bag. When swimming to the depths of the ocean, some disgusting survivors will suck on the bladders of a tamed diplocaulus' head as an effective oxygen source.

diplodocus.name: Diplocaulus(笠头螈)
diplodocus.desc: The Diplocaulus(笠头螈) is a smaller sauropod best known for its ten-person (plus one driver) saddle, making it an excellent dino for group transport.

doedicurus.name: Doedicurus(星尾兽)
doedicurus.desc: Note: The Doedicurus(星尾兽) can gather Obsidian from a small number of rocks, such as the ones on the volcano on The Island. It cannot gather Obsidian from most usual Obsidian rocks.

dragon.name: Dragon(双足飞龙)
dragon.tamingNotice: The Dragon is one of the three bosses. Have a good strategy on how to battle Dragon? Share a tip!

electrophorus.name: Electrophorus(电鳗)
electrophorus.desc: The Electrophorus(电鳗) is an electric eel with the ability to shock its targets.

equus.name: Equus(马)
equus.tamingNotice: To tame the Equus(马), you must mount it immediately after the first feeding. Tap the action button each time you're prompted to feed again.
equus.desc: The Equus(马) is a horse-like creature that can be mounted with special saddles. While mounted, survivors can use whips and lassos.

eurypterid.name: Eurypterid(广翅鲎)
eurypterid.tamingNotice: The Eurypterid(广翅鲎) is not tamable. It can be found on the bottom of the ocean floor.

featherlight.name: Featherlight(轻羽鸟)
featherlight.desc: The Featherlight(轻羽鸟) is a tamable bird-like creature in Ark: Aberration.

gallimimus.name: Gallimimus(似鸡龙)
gallimimus.desc: The Gallimimus(似鸡龙) is extremely fragile, but its power to outrun everything gained place in the hearts of survivors who look for a mount to explore and scout the island by land, or just want to evade battle. This creature is unable to harvest most resources or attack enemy, but its reputation as fastest creature sure make it a valuable mount.

giantbee.name: Giant Bee(巨蜂)
giantbee.desc: The Giant Bee(巨蜂) builds its nest at the tops of Redwood trees. While it's not an easy task, a nest can be broken open and the queen can be tamed. Once tamed, she will generate honey as well as lay drone eggs.
giantbee.tamingNotice: To tame a Queen Giant Bee(巨蜂), you must first destroy her nest. The nest has 5,000 health.

glowbug.name: Glowbug(萤火虫)
glowbug.tamingNotice: The Glowbug(萤火虫) is a firefly-like creature in Ark: Aberration.
glowbug.desc: The Glowbug(萤火虫) is a firefly-like creature in Ark: Aberration. Creatures with charges can extract a charge from Glowbug(萤火虫)s. They can be found in all biomes other than the surface.

glowtail.name: Glowtail(耀尾兽)
glowtail.tamingNotice: The Glowtail(耀尾兽) is a lizard-like creature in Ark: Aberration.
glowtail.desc: The Glowtail(耀尾兽) is a lizard-like creature in Ark: Aberration.

hesperornis.name: Hesperornis(黄昏鸟)
hesperornis.tamingNotice: To tame a Hesperornis(黄昏鸟), you must kill a fish, and drag the fish's corpse to the Hesperornis(黄昏鸟) to feed it. The fish's size plays a major factor in how many fish will be required (a 1.0x fish appears to fill up the taming bar twice as much as a 0.5x fish). Level of fish does not appear to impact taming. The Sabertooth(剑齿虎) Salmon is by far the most effective fish, equivalent of about 4 Coels of the same size, while the Piranha(食人鱼) is equivalent to about 2.4 Coels.
hesperornis.desc: The Hesperornis(黄昏鸟) is a flightless aquatic bird.

hyaenodon.name: Hyaenodon(鬣齿兽)
hyaenodon.desc: The Hyaenodon(鬣齿兽) is a Hyaena-like creature.

ichthyornis.name: Ichthyornis(鱼鸟)
ichthyornis.desc: The Ichthyornis(鱼鸟) is a seagull that can be tamed to fetch fish.

iguanodon.name: Iguanodon(禽龙)
iguanodon.desc: The Iguanodon(禽龙) is a dinosaur with the unique ability to walk on either two or four legs. When walking on two, it can attack enemies with its front feet, and while walking on four, it can sprint without running out of stamina. The Iguanodon(禽龙) also has the ability to convert fruit and vegetables into seeds.

jerboa.name: Jerboa(跳鼠)
jerboa.desc: While the Jerboa has little practical use, some survivors enjoy its companionship as a cuddly, shoulder-mounted pet. This mini kangaroo-like creature is able to sense upcoming weather changes and its behavior will indicate when a tribe might need to prepare. The Jerboa is easy to tame, however, low torpor means survivors need to pay close attention to it while taming.

kaprosuchus.name: Kaprosuchus(猪鳄)
kaprosuchus.desc: The Kaprosuchus(猪鳄) is a crocodile-like reptile commonly found around swamps. Though it is a smaller, weaker version of the Sarco(帝鳄), some survivors perfer it for its speed — both on land and in water.

karkinos.name: Karkinos(巨蟹怪)
karkinos.tamingNotice: The Karkinos(巨蟹怪) is a creature in Ark: Aberration.
karkinos.desc: The Karkinos(巨蟹怪) is a massive crab-like creature in Ark: Aberration that can grab and smash creatures and players. It can also throw them at great lengths. Using its strong legs, the Karkinos(巨蟹) can leap to impressive heights.

kentrosaurus.name: Kentrosaurus(肯氏龙)
kentrosaurus.desc: While the Kentrosaurus(肯氏龙) may appear to just be a version of the Stegosaurus(剑龙), its strength should not be mistaken. With its sharp defensive spikes and deadly tail, the Kentrosaurus(肯氏龙) can even take on larger carnivores — especially when in herds. Because of its sharp spines, saddling a Kentrosaurus(肯氏龙) is not possible.

lamprey.name: Lamprey(七鳃鳗)
lamprey.tamingNotice: The Lamprey(七鳃鳗) can only be tamed using a Fish Basket in Aberration.
lamprey.desc: The Lamprey(七鳃鳗) is a leech-like creature in Aberration.

leedsichthys.name: Leedsichthys(利兹鱼)
leedsichthys.tamingNotice: The Leedsichthys(利兹鱼) cannot be tamed, however, it can be trapped so that tribes can scrape off 优质生肉 from its body without killing it.

liopleurodon.name: Liopleurodon(滑齿龙)
liopleurodon.desc: The Liopleurodon(滑齿龙) is a aquatic reptile often found hiding in the reefs of the ocean.

lymantria.name: Lymantria(飞蛾)
lymantria.desc: The Lymantria(飞蛾) is a moth-like creature that can expel a cloud of poisonous spores. While its slow flying speed make it a less suitable flying mount for transportation, survivors can use its spores to slow down enemies.

lystrosaurus.name: Lystrosaurus(水龙兽)
lystrosaurus.desc: The Lystrosaurus is a small, common herbivore often used as a pet. While the Lystrosaurus will not fight, it can be useful to have around — or as a companion on short hunting trips — as it increases experience of nearby creatures and survivors. The Lystrosaurus must be tamed passively, making it very easy to acquire by any survivor with a handful of 稀有花朵s.

manticore.name: Manticore(狮蝎)
manticore.tamingNotice: The Manticore(狮蝎) is a boss in Scorched Earth. Have a good strategy on how to battle Manticore(狮蝎)? Share a tip!

megalosaurus.name: Megalosaurus(斑龙)
megalosaurus.desc: The megalosaurus is one of the strongest therapods, but its nocturnal sleeping pattern make it significantly less effective during the day. The megalosaurus can bite and even latch onto enemies — including humans — and swing them around, hindering their ability to move. This carnivore is stronger than a Carno or a Rex at night, but during the day, it is much more slow and sluggish.

megapithecus.name: Megapithecus(金刚)
megapithecus.tamingNotice: The Megapithecus(金刚) is one of the three bosses in Ark. Have a good strategy on how to battle Megapithecus(金刚)? Share a tip!

microraptor.name: Microraptor(小盗龙)
microraptor.desc: The Microraptor(小盗龙) is a tiny, agile dinosaur with the ability to attack predators while ignoring their mounts. Its wings also give it the ability to glide after leaping.

morellatops.name: Morellatops(驼峰兽)
morellatops.desc: The Morellatops(驼峰兽) is a camel-like creature that has the ability to store water in its hump. It can be essential as a pack animal when transporting supplies through the hot, dry desert. The Morellatops(驼峰兽) will flee once attacked, but once knocked out, it is a relatively easy creature to tame.

mosasaurus.name: Mosasaurus(沧龙)
mosasaurus.desc: An elusive marine lizard and reputed as one of the largest creature found in the waters, the Mosasaurus(沧龙) is much more powerful than any known aquatic beast encountered in the depth. While its sluggish speed may put off some survivors, being ambushed by one can mean a certain death.

moschops.name: Moschops(麝足兽)
moschops.tamingNotice: The Moschops(麝足兽) eats Sap, Giant Bee(巨蜂) Honey, Leech Blood, Rare Mushrooms, 稀有花朵s, Organic Polymer, 优质生肉, and 优质生鱼肉. Each time you feed it, its desired food will change. Have a good Moschops(麝足兽) taming technique? Share a tip!
moschops.desc: The Moschops(麝足兽) is a omnivorous therapsid best known for its love for food. Survivors can train it to favour specific types of food — whether it be Prime Meat or 稀有花朵s — and it will become more effective at gathering it. The Moschops(麝足兽) is a very cowardly creature and will flee from any sight of danger.

nameless.name: Nameless(无名怪)
nameless.tamingNotice: The Nameless(无名怪) is an untamable creature in Ark: Aberration.
nameless.desc: The Nameless(无名怪) is an untamable chupacabra-like creature in Ark: Aberration. The alpha Nameless(无名怪) will slowly spawn other Nameless(无名怪) over time.

otter.name: Otter(水獭)
otter.tamingNotice: To tame an otter, kill some fish, approach the otter, and then use the action button to feed the fish to it. Level of fish does not impact taming. The Sabertooth(剑齿虎) Salmon is by far the most effective fish, followed by the Piranha(食人鱼) and the Coelacanth(腔棘鱼). Please ignore timing and effectiveness as calculations are not yet complete.

overseer.name: Overseer(监视者)
overseer.tamingNotice: The Overseer(监视者) is the final boss in Ark: Survival Evolved. This creature's Dodo(渡渡鸟)dex profile may contain spoilers. Have a good strategy on how to battle The Overseer(监视者)? Share a tip!

ovis.name: Ovis(绵羊)
ovis.desc: The ovis is a sheep-like creature that many survivors find useful in farming. It can be found in the grasslands. While rare, it can be tamed simply by feeding it one 甜蔬菜饼. This sheep can be sheered with Scissors to obtain Wool, or killed to obtain Mutton. While the ovis can be mounted, it is not an ideal mount for transport and provides very little use once mounted, other than its ability to climb up steep inclines.

pachyrhinosaurus.name: Pachyrhinosaurus(厚鼻龙)
pachyrhinosaurus.desc: The Pachy(肿头龙)rhinosaurus is a herbivore with a unique ability to manipulate its enemies. This cunning dinosaur can emit two types of mists that manipulates most nearby creatures to be either passive or aggressive. This allows survivors to safely travel through a dangerous area or even herd a group of vicious creatures to use against an enemy. The Pachy(肿头龙)rhinosaurus is slightly larger than the Triceratops(三角龙), and wears a two-person saddle once tamed.

pegomastax.name: Pegomastax(双坚颌龙)
pegomastax.desc: The Pegomastax(双坚颌龙) is a small herbivore popular among farmers. The Pegomastax(双坚颌龙) has an exceptional skill of gathering seeds and berries, while also able to gather rare ingredients such as 稀有花朵s and Rare Mushrooms. While it is relatively weak, this small dinosaur will become quite agressive if provoked.

pelagornis.name: Pelagornis(伪齿鸟)
pelagornis.desc: The Pelagornis(伪齿鸟) is a versatile pelican-like bird and the only creature able to walk, fly, and surface-swim.

phoenix.name: Phoenix(凤凰)
phoenix.tamingNotice: To tame a Phoenix(凤凰), shoot it with a flame arrow, flamethrower or Fire Wyvern(飞龙). Weapon quality impacts taming speed; a 200% damage bow will be twice as fast as a 100% bow. Please ignore taming effectiveness and taming times as the Phoenix(凤凰) has unique calculations. Have a good taming technique idea? Share a tip!

phiomia.name: Phiomia(渐新象)
phiomia.desc: While the Phiomia(渐新象) does not attack, many survivors see value in it as an easy-to-tame pack animal. It will quickly flee when attempting to knock it out, but once tranquilized, the Phiomia(渐新象) can be tamed very quickly, making it a popular choice for survivors looking for a creature to transport supplies. The Phiomia(渐新象) produces a lot of feces in comparison to other creatures, making it useful in fertilizer production.

piranha.name: Piranha(食人鱼)
piranha.tamingNotice: The Piranha(食人鱼) can only be tamed using a Fish Basket in Aberration.

pteranodon.name: Pteranodon(翼龙)
pteranodon.desc: The pteranodon is a fast and versatile flying mount useful for traveling and scouting, though not always the ideal choice for battle. Knocking a pteranodon out doesn't take much, but can still be a challenge since it will immediately flee after being attacked. Once knocked out, taming is quite easy in comparison to other creatures, and with its low saddle requirements, this makes it an especially popular creature for newer survivors while still being versatile enough for more experienced survivors. What the pterandon lacks in stamina, weight, and health, it makes up with its speed.

purlovia.name: Purlovia(兽头龙)
purlovia.desc: The Purlovia(兽头龙) is a mammal with the unique ability to burrow underground and hibrinate. Using the technique, the Purlovia(兽头龙) will pounce once a predator appears nearby.

quetzal.name: Quetzal(风神翼龙)
quetzal.desc: The Quetzal(风神翼龙) is a behemoth of a creature with base stats that top the charts (health, stamina, weight, and torpor). The Quetzal(风神翼龙)'s platform saddle make it an excellent choice for a mobile air base or even a caravan for transporting and gathering metal and other supplies on harder to reach areas. While its melee strength isn't as high as some might expect, its health and ability to carry weapons make it suitable to use as a war bird. Its preference for Rex Kibble make it difficult to tame, and even more so difficult to knock out in the air.

raptor.name: Raptor(迅猛龙)
raptor.desc: The Raptor(迅猛龙) is a well-rounded and easy-to-tame dinosaur. Its high speed and ability to defend itself make it very useful for travel, especially for newer survivors. While the raptor has a lower torpor tolerance, its speed can often make it difficult to target.

ravager.name: Ravager(劫掠者)
ravager.desc: The Ravager(劫掠者) is a tamable creature in Ark: Aberration.

reaper.name: Reaper(死神)
reaper.tamingNotice: To tame a Reaper(死神), you must get a Reaper(死神) Queen to impregnate you. Visit the Tips section to see detailed strategies — or add your own!
reaper.desc: The Reaper(死神) King and Queen are creatures in Ark: Aberration.

rockdrake.name: Rock Drake(岩龙)
rockdrake.tamingNotice: The Rock Drake(岩龙) must be tamed like the Wyvern(飞龙). To acquire one, you must steal and raise its egg.
rockdrake.desc: The Rock Drake(岩龙) is a gliding creature that has the ability to cloak itself and its rider. Using a Rock Drake(岩龙)'s excellent climbing skills, survivors can traverse across steep cliffs. The Rock Drake(岩龙) can only be found in a particular cavern and is relatively tough to tame.

rockelemental.name: Rock Elemental(石头人)
rockelemental.note: 7.5 provides a better estimate, because sometimes TE starts at 89.5%?
rockelemental.tamingNotice: To knock out a Rock Elemental(石头人), you must target its head.
rockelemental.desc: The Rock Elemental is a massive rock monster that is typically found disguised as a stone formation. When a survivor enters its territory, it will begin thrashing and throwing large boulders. Once tamed, it can be a highly effective siege weapon to bring into battle.

rollrat.name: Roll Rat(滚地鼠)
rollrat.tamingNotice: To tame a Roll Rat(滚地鼠), wait until it burrows and underground then drop a food item into its burrow.
eats: Giant Bee(巨蜂)巨蜂蜜|Roll Rat(滚地鼠)
rollrat.desc: The Roll Rat(滚地鼠) is a tamable, rideable mole-like creature in Ark: Aberration. Almost like a more powerful Doedicurus(星尾兽), you can rapidly roll while mounted, plowing through enemies in its path with its spiked saddle. This advanced metal saddle can seat 6 survivors and must be repaired after repeatedly rolling.

sabertoothsalmon.name: SabertoothSalmon(剑齿鲑鱼)
sabertoothsalmon.tamingNotice: The SabertoothSalmon(剑齿鲑鱼) can only be tamed using a Fish Basket in Aberration.

seeker.name: Seeker(追寻者)
seeker.tamingNotice: The Seeker(追寻者) is an untamable creature in Ark: Aberration. Submit a tip about this creature!
seeker.desc: The Seeker(追寻者) is a creature in Ark: Aberration.

shinehorn.name: Shinehorn(闪角鹿)
shinehorn.tamingNotice: The Shinehorn(闪角鹿) is a creature in Ark: Aberration.
shinehorn.desc: The Shinehorn(闪角鹿) is a jackalope-like creature in Ark: Aberration.

tapejara.name: Tapejara(古神翼龙)
tapejara.desc: The Tapejara(古神翼龙) is a versatile and highly maneuverable pterosaur known for its three-person saddle. While it may not have as much stamina and weight carrying capacity as other creatures, it has unique benefits in combat. The Tapejara(古神翼龙) can land on trees and other vertical surfaces, allowing both the pilot and the passengers to use weapons. Its rudder-like fin make it the only flying creature able to hover and strafe side-to-side.

therizinosaurus.name: Therizinosaurus(镰刀龙)
therizinosaurus.desc: The Tickle Chicken (also known by its more boring, scientific name, Therizinosaurus(镰刀龙)) is a medium-sized, agressive dinosaur. While it is slow and cannot carry much weight, it is a quite versatile mount, being very strong in battle and having the ability to gather resources effectively. The Therizinosaurus(镰刀龙) can be trained to gather specific types of resources for its rider.

thylacoleo.name: Thylacoleo(袋狮)
thylacoleo.desc: The Thylacoleo(袋狮) is a large, powerful mount that can climb up trees and pounce on its enemies.

titanoboa.name: Titanoboa(泰坦巨蟒)
titanoboa.tamingNotice: These values are egg-stracted from Dodo(渡渡鸟)dex's own tests and user reports. Timing and intervals are rough estimates, as the Titanoboa(泰坦巨蟒)'s eating pattern is unclear. Use the 'Report Data Error' button if any of your eggs differ. The Titanoboa(泰坦巨蟒) must be tamed with fertilized eggs. Drop an egg near it and it will consume it.

titanosaur.name: Titanosaur(泰坦巨龙)
titanosaur.tamingNotice: To knock out a Titanosaur(泰坦巨龙), you must target its head.
titanosaur.desc: The Titanosaur(泰坦巨龙) is the largest creature in Ark whose stats top the charts across the board. This sauropod's massive platform saddle allows tribes to build large fortresses on its back — if they're skilled enough to tame it.

trilobite.name: Trilobite(三叶虫)
trilobite.tamingNotice: The Trilobite(三叶虫) can only be tamed using a Fish Basket in Aberration.

tusoteuthis.name: Tusoteuthis(托斯特巨鱿)
tusoteuthis.desc: The Tusoteuthis(托斯特巨鱿) is a massive, aggressive squid found in the depths of the oceans. In battle, the Tusoteuthis(托斯特巨鱿) can grab its prey and knock it unconcious, siphoning its blood to gain health. Once tamed, the ink from a Tusoteuthis(托斯特巨鱿) can be used as a constant Oil source. Some survivors choose to hunt the Tusoteuthis(托斯特巨鱿) for its Oil.
tusoteuthis.tamingNotice: The Tusoteuthis(托斯特巨鱿)'s taming method differs from most creatures. Please ignore its interval and time calculations.

woollyrhino.name: Wyvern(飞龙)
woollyrhino.tamingNotice: To tame a Wyvern(飞龙), survivors must steal a Wyvern(飞龙) egg. Once hatched, Wyvern(飞龙) babies need to be fed Wyvern(飞龙) Milk, which can be obtained by knocking out a female Wyvern(飞龙).
woollyrhino.desc: The Wyvern(飞龙) is a highly sought-after massive flying dragon that can overpower most creatures it faces. The deadly Wyvern(飞龙), which is only tamable by stealing and raising as a baby, can be found in three varieities — Fire, Lightning, and Poison — each of which have distinct attacks.

yeti.name: Yeti(雪人)
yeti.tamingNotice: The Yeti(雪人) is an Alpha creature found in the Snow Cave. It cannot be tamed.
